      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of June 23 article on historic theaters, which misstated history of Ford's Theater, Washington</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Weekend on June 23 about historic theaters misstated the history of Ford's Theater in Washington. The building was not torn down after the assassination of President Abraham Lincoln. It was gutted and the interior became office space in the 1930's, but the walls were left standing. A restoration of the theater began in 1965, based on photographs taken by Mathew Brady, and the new Ford's opened in 1968.</p>
      </block>
